.<br>
1. Minimium orbital velocity is 8000 meters per second + 400<br>
meters per second from the earths rotation (east to west)<br>
near the equater. This about 18,000 miles per hour.<br>
<br>
2. Velocity to reach orbit around the moon  is<br>
about 11,200 meters per second.<br>
<br>
3. Minimium earth escape velocity is 11,600 meters per<br>
second which is 24,600 miles per hour.<br>
<br>
4. Earths velocity around the sun is about<br>
30 kilometers per second 67,000 mile per hour.<br>
<br>
5. Mimimium solar system escape velocity is <br>
93,500 miles per hour relatative to the sun<br>
<br>
5. The launch window to mars, and venus opens up every<br>
odd year from 7-24 to 9-7.The launch window is created by the alignment of the planets.<br>
<br>
6. The next mars - venus launch window is<br>
7-24-2003 to 9-7-2003 .<br>
Flight time on hoffman orbit to venus is 90-120 days<br>
Flight time on hoffman orbit to mars is 8-10 months.<br>
<br>
7.  To go to mars on hoffman orbit  you must accelerate <br>
to at least  12000  meters per second and launch east<br>
 to west. <br>
<br>
  Then you get 12,000 meters per second + 400<br>
,meters per second from earths rotation. You then achieve <br>
12,400 meters per second which is about 26,400 miles per hour. This gives you a hyperbolic excess velocity of 1800<br>
mile per hour. Now you are bound for mars.But you must slow down by at least  3300 meters per second to orbit mars or if you do not you will  fly by mars instead of orbiting it.<br>
<br>
 If that happens you will then continue outward until you fall<br>
into Jupiters gravity field. The you will come in behind Jupiter and  be flung outward at velocity 2V like the pioneer and voyager probes. Jupiter orbits  the sun at about 29,000 miles an hour so you would be flung outward at 58,000 miles per hour + your own velocity. Then Jupiter will take back 29,000 miles per hour and you will be flung out of the solar system with your remaining delta v.<br>
<br>
 If you want to go to venus you accelerate to 12,000<br>
meters  per second and you launch from west to east.<br>
This cause you to loose 400 meters per second from<br>
the earths rotaion and you then are pulled inside the orbit of the earth around the sun by the suns gravity.<br>
Now you are bound for the planet Venus..<br>
